LAKERS at SPURS | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | October 26, 2021

The Los Angeles Lakers defeated the San Antonio Spurs in overtime, 125-121. Anthony Davis (35 PTS, 17 REB, 4 BLK) and Russell Westbrook (33 PTS, 10 REB, 8 AST) combined for 68 PTS for the Lakers, while Dejounte Murray tallied 21 PTS, 12 REB and a career-high 15 AST for the Spurs in the losing effort, his 5th career triple-double. The Lakers improve to 2-2 on the season, while the Spurs fall to 1-3.

Next Games:
Los Angeles Lakers at Oklahoma City Thunder - Oct.27th at 8pm/et on NBA League Pass
San Antonio Spurs at Dallas Mavericks - Oct.28th at 8:30pm/et on NBA League Pass

next.excerpt:
Today AD brings you to the lush hillside neighborhood of Los Feliz in Los Angeles to visit the enchanting home of actress Vanessa Hudgens. Hudgens spent five years searching for the right property before settling upon the Georgian colonial house she now calls home, undertaking renovations both on her own and in tandem with interior designer Jake Arnold. With her work comes many nights on the road (she stars in Lin Manuel Miranda’s upcoming directorial debut, “Tick, Tick...Boom!”) meaning Vanessa’s home has become a place to return to, renew, and reconnect. “It’s nice to know that when I get home, I’ll have a bath waiting for me. I always savor that first soak.”

See more of Vanessa's home here: https://www.architecturaldigest.com/gallery/inside-vanessa-hudgens-los-feliz-home

Vanessa's a big fan of her Cali Water fridge and you can be too: https://drinkcaliwater.com/

Artwork courtesy of:
Photos from Children of the Lost Sun by Asher Moss
https://www.twiinlake.com/children-of-the-lost-sun/children-of-the-lost-sun-by-twiin-lake
http://www.ashermoss.com/

Libre Pensador by Fernando Garcia Rosas
http://fernandogarciarosas.com/

Rugs seen throughout the house courtesy of: https://www.lawrenceoflabrea.com/

Catch Vanessa in "Tick, Tick...Boom!" in theaters November 12th and on Netflix November 19th
